      <p>When someone passes away in the UAE—or when UAE assets are involved in an inheritance—the Personal Status Court requires translated vital records. Death certificates establish the passing. Birth certificates establish who the heirs are. Marriage certificates establish spousal rights. These translations directly affect how assets are distributed.</p>
      
      <h3>Status Changes and Updates</h3>
      <p>Life changes require documentation. A divorce certificate updates your marital status for future marriage applications. A death certificate removes a deceased family member from records. A birth certificate for a newborn starts their official record. We help with translations for all life transitions.</p>
